properties.headline: FLOODING - SINGLETON New England Highway
properties.adviceB: Avoid the area; 	Never drive through floodwater
properties.otherAdvice: Residents and Emergency vehicles travelling in light vehicles can travel from Muswellbrook to Singleton via the New England Hwy and can then use the local diversions to continue their journey.
properties.diversions:
Northbound: Golden Hwy, Denman Rd, Sydney Rd to Muswellbrook.  
Southbound: Sydney St (Muswellbrook) Denman Rd, Golden Hwy.
This diversion is suitable for all vehicles.

 

Local diversions at Singleton are in place either side of the Hunter River (Residents & Emergency vehicles only):
Northbound: Queen to Gresford Rd, Dyrring Rd, Pioneer Rd, Bridgemen Rd, Blaxland Ave, and White Ave. 
Southbound: White Ave, Blaxland Ave, Bridgeman Rd, Pioneer Rd, Dyrring Rd, Gresford Rd over the bridge to Queen St.
